# Design System Rules

- Follow Material Design 3 principles: clear hierarchy, consistent spacing, accessible interactions.
- Use design tokens from `src/styles/tokens.css`; avoid hardcoded colors, spacing, and radius values.
- Keep component APIs semantic and minimal (`variant`, `size`, `tone`).
- Ensure focus-visible styles exist for interactive elements.
- Keep typography to system variants only: `headline`, `body1`, `body2`, `button`, `caption`.
- Prefer composition with layout primitives (`Container`, `Flex`, `Stack`) before custom wrappers.
